The TEM images of SGCD, TiO2-CD, ECH-CH-TiO2-CD and EDA-CH-TiO2-CD are shown in Fig. 4
                        . The size of the SGCD and TiO2-CD from TEM results are in between 8–10 nm and 100–120 nm. The utilization of EDA as a crosslinker results in a reduction in the size of the overall composite to a range of 50–60 nm. It is due to the proper arrangement of the Ti-O network over the biopolymer, which ultimately reduces the accumulation of nanoparticles. The surface morphology (Fig. 5
                        ) shows that TiO2 nanoparticles are uniform and spherical. This uniformity remains the same when it is incorporated and crosslinked with EDA. Further, the composite structure shows a more porous structure before adsorption than after BG and MR dye adsorption. EDX mapping of EDA-modified chitosan composite shows 21 wt% Ti, 18.27 % C, 7.6 % N, and 59.97 % O (Fig. 6
                        ).
